    "Figure 7 illustrates the graphical results for two Peruvian departments: Loreto and Madre de Dios.",
    "appreciated quite well in the outbreak happening in 2019 for all the six reported FUs of Brazil, where the peaks of the observed cases (green curve) are properly followed by the ensemble prediction (red curve).",
    "Furthermore, the predictions of the ensemble model have generally lower uncertainty compared to the other mode, as can be seen by their 95% CI over the validation period.",
    "The small confidence interval is another advantage of the proposed ensemble model, as it guarantees that the model inferences are reliable and do not diverge too much from the observed cases.",
    "The generalisation ability of the ensemble model is still limited for those regions reporting DIR values outside the main behaviour found in the training set."
